					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1814684&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164672" alt="GreenWolf" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1814684)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/greenwolf" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1814684); return false;" >GreenWolf</a></span> <span class="odate time_1457317603 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">07 Mar 2016 02:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2468554">
									

<p>A few notes on costs:</p>
<ul>
<li>First off, this is written back in the late 80s. While inflation hasn't been bad enough that money was worth an order of magnitude more back then, money was definitely worth more back then than it is now.</li>
<li>Second, PL has access to resources that many organizations don't. Who knows what kind of cost-cutting paratech they have lying around.</li>
<li>Third, costs are going to tend to be on the optimistic side, while still being within realistic (for PL) estimates. This'll drop the numbers a bit.</li>
</ul>

							</div>

								
