														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3782263">
									

<p>Really neat! I love the format and am curious if the author has some degree of background in biomedical or the like. The ambition suits the GOI well, too.</p>
<p>Gotta agree with everyone saying the costs are too low by an order of magnitude, though. I've worked in some basic research myself and everything is stupid expensive. The animal testing I could buy if they're being shady/sloppy, but most of the equipment would have to be custom made, multiplying the cost. For reference, a bog-standard MRI machine still goes for about a million (plus hundreds of thousands more for the room it sits in), and a steel crucible you'd find in a factory is closer to 15 mil.</p>
<p>Regardless, you get some degree of belief-stretching artistic license with this sort of thing. The whole associated set of entries make for a fun read.</p>

							</div>

								
					
